Hi LC.  Thanks so much.  All (well, most) of the images on my site were done using my 
water technique (link to instructions on lower left of page 2 of the site).  I do have a couple 
of crystal collages (also page 2, lower right - if you click on either image, a collage will 
pop up).  I have gotten, as I recall, a dog in one of the crystal shots.

So far, I&#39;ve found that the citrine quartz works well if it has lots of lines in it (I don&#39;t know 
what the technical term is, occlusions?  Inclusions??) rather than being clear.  These seems 
to give them something to use to show themselves, if that makes sense.  I can actually 
watch them appearing my view finder, but usually can&#39;t photograph what I&#39;m seeing.  
Might try videoing the crystal like I do with my water technique to see if that helps.

With the water, I never see what is coming through until I go back and review the session, 
one frame at a time.  Sometimes I get a whole lotta nothing, and other times I&#39;m totally 
blown away by the clarity of an image.  I hope some member here will try it.  :-)

Margaret

